ort of arena combat, man pitted against man and sometimes beast in a grisly bout to the death. An unholy marriage between Hotline Miami's sadistic lust for blood and FTL's time-wasting strategy and management. Domina takes the brutality of gladiatorial combat and gives it an addictive layer.\n\nDomina with its visceral and gritty portrayal envoked a hard to admit instinct-driven sadistic side of my gaming fixations, instilling a certain kind of excitement for the sport of blood that sits macabrely at the root of humanity and its violent history. The feeling is just so intensely real despite its low-fi visual style, mostly lent to by the gruff and mature handling of situations and dialogue. Lines that don't hold back on the adult language or the mature situations made Domina feel like something right out of a Frank Miller graphic novel.\n\nThe heavy and pulsing soundtrack driving the banquet of blood and evisceration, the gore and the disregard for life in favor of entertainment and profit, Domina makes a strong argument for the case that maybe humanity's history has only ever been capable of death and destruction from the beginning. The same high-energy and infectiously melodic electronic jams you would expect from bignic are here in full force now with arabesque horns and strings wonderfully winding their way into the mix for a heavy and esoteric sound befitting of its period.\n\nAll in all, if you admire the brutality of combat sports, or dig the history behind gladiatorial colloseums, or you're just a big bloodthirsty freak who wants to spill more blood for the Blood Gods, Dominic is your bloodsport simulator for sure.", "comment_count": 4, "received_for_free": true, "voted_up": true, "recommendationid": "45919012", "weighted_vote_score": "0.723108172416687012", "votes_up": 27, "steam_purchase": false, "timestamp_updated": 1542747346, "written_during_early_access": false, "votes_funny": 1}, {"timestamp_created": 1542735962, "language": "english", "author": {"stea