ke a name for your ludas and gain both the adoration of the crowd and admission to the games by winning three required regional championships before the year ends.\n\nGameplay revovles around training these gladiators and fighting them in the arena.  The game allows a \"mind control\" upgrade that has you personally control your gladiator, but seems best suited for allowing the player to take a passenger seat during the events and allowing the AI to fight based on the stats of the combatant.  \n\nAlong with the purchasing of slaves to train as gladiators you also hire employees to oversee more upgrade-oriented aspects of the ludas. The game boasts a fairly large upgrade gold-sink system that has you always needing more and requiring you to strategically use what's available to you.  Slots for available employees are limited, so your overall ludas begins to develop a \"build\" along with each individual gladiator.  \n\nDomina plays in what is generally referred to as a \"rogue-like\" or \"ironman\" system that has the game auto-saving as often as possible to force the player to stick with the outcomes. \n\nI generally only write reviews for games that I would recommend and Domina falls into that category.  I would suggest this to players up to the challenge.  But be warned:  it can be a frustrating game.", "comment_count": 0, "received_for_free": false, "voted_up": true, "recommendationid": "45112470", "weighted_vote_score": 0, "votes_up": 0, "steam_purchase": true, "timestamp_updated": 1538721678, "written_during_early_access": false, "votes_funny": 0}, {"timestamp_created": 1538625961, "language": "english", "author": {"steamid": "76561198073346678", "playtime_forever": 2886, "last_played": 1538799028, "num_reviews": 3, "num_games_owned": 67, "playtime_last_two_weeks": 0}, "review": "Great game.", "comment_count": 0, "received_for_free": false, "voted_up": true, "recommendationid": "45094391", "weighted_vote_score": 0, "votes_up": 0, "steam_purchase": true, "timest