s and it's as much fun to watch the visceral action unfold, as it's to whop other gladiators yourself.\n\nWhile the game can be rather easy on lower difficulties, it can quickly become punishing on the higher ones. Decisions have to be made with care and foresight, or you might quickly find yourself without gladiators, starved out, dehydrated and sorely lacking in wine. One of the great things is that no matter how harsh a blow you're dealt, if you're smart about it, there's almost always a way to recover. This makes the decision-making very satisfying.\n\nAlso, the extensive support from the game's dev should be commended. When Domina was first released and it seemed to suffer from massive issues, I was doubtful and it took quite a while until I eventually picked the game up. There may still be some minor bugs hidden in the crevices that go mostly unnoticed, but even a year later, the dev not only works hard to squash them all out, but also adds new content and features that enrich the existing gameplay. You don't see that sort of commitment often.\n\nUltimately, I can definitely recommend the game - for the current price, it's a steal. In a sale, you can do no wrong.", "comment_count": 0, "received_for_free": false, "voted_up": true, "recommendationid": "44463979", "weighted_vote_score": 0, "votes_up": 0, "steam_purchase": true, "timestamp_updated": 1535631393, "written_during_early_access": false, "votes_funny": 0}, {"timestamp_created": 1535566208, "language": "english", "author": {"steamid": "76561198352744111", "playtime_forever": 5339, "last_played": 1550996969, "num_reviews": 2, "num_games_owned": 38, "playtime_last_two_weeks": 0}, "review": "Extremely addictive with a lot of playbackability. Need slight balancing as well as some adjustments to some cards, but overall a great game", "comment_count": 0, "received_for_free": false, "voted_up": true, "recommendationid": "44448451", "weighted_vote_score": 0, "votes_up": 0, "steam_purchase": true, "timestamp_upda