ash games / Browser games this is right up your ally. \n\nThe game simple in nature but you can play it in different ways. You can change alot of settings in this game to suit the difficulty level you want, or if you want to play casually or more in depth. People who complain about the game difficulty or playstyle never bothered to tinker with the settings; you can make it dim-wittingly easy, or so difficult that you have fits of manic-depressive laughter. Due to the type of game you can easily come up with your own rules to abide by or play through the game a 2nd time around with a completely different approach.\n\nSays I have played 16 hours but it honestly felt like double that. I remember several evenings where I played much longer than I should have, instead of sleeping!\n\nThis is a pretty good, deep, game at 5 bucks. You have to really like management style games if it's priced at it's regular 10 bucks.\n\nThis is a unique game with a charm of it's own. It's been updated constantly by a developer that is clearly passionate about what they made.", "comment_count": 0, "received_for_free": false, "voted_up": true, "recommendationid": "43069738", "weighted_vote_score": "0.519999980926513672", "votes_up": 1, "steam_purchase": true, "timestamp_updated": 1530022454, "written_during_early_access": false, "votes_funny": 0}, {"timestamp_created": 1529901007, "language": "english", "author": {"steamid": "76561198005033178", "playtime_forever": 412, "last_played": 1529835383, "num_reviews": 4, "num_games_owned": 55, "playtime_last_two_weeks": 0}, "review": "For 2usd during steam sale, this game is well worth it, but for the full price? i'm not sure.\n\nThe gameplay itself was fun and the soundtrack will get you hyped, but don't expect any story since it's quite short. It was interesting for 2-3 runs and that's about it. I wish there would be more additional contents as I think this game has the potential to prolong the story more.", "comment_count": 0, "received_for_free