combat. You also research a tech tree, and can recruit up to three employees from a decent list, each of whom have unique benefits. One gripe I have is that some employees are just explicitly better or worse than others, kind of forcing your hand in the end. Not having the blacksmith character (can't recall its latin name) is a terrible idea, so one of your slots is basically taken up automatically by him. \n\nOne of the early researches allows you to 'mind control' a gladiator, taking manual control, but honestly the AI were way better than I was so I never used that utility. Cool idea, but the pacing of the game was one where a computer kinda had me beat at least. This means that the AI control stat for each gladiator is incredibly important, and always the first one you want to level. This is not encouraged by the game by default, as it sets the training for it to 0 with all new gladiators. Little things like that where Domina doesn't help you a lot to learn, or actively points you in the wrong direction in some ways, are part of why I gave only a good score as opposed to a great one.\n\nSpeaking of combat, I would recommend to enable \"Brutal Combat\" in the options. It makes the fights actually last any duration, where without it many fights lasted literally less than a second. Brutal combat lessens all damage done, allowing for more intrigue in a match, and giving lesser champions at least a fighting chance.\n\nThis review is already getting long, so this'll be the last thing about content that I mention. The goal of the game is to defeat at least three regional champions through a seperate map, to qualify for the Grand Championship that happens after one year. One small gripe I had was that the regional champions were often *easier* than some of the early normal match-ups, which was certainly not what I expected or what made sense to me. It certainly made it more possible to get to the finish of the game, but it was a little strange. Its possible that was simply an effect of the default difficulty, but I'm not sure. Without giving spoilers, though, the final championship battle is not the end of the game. A twist occurs that I thoroughly enjoyed, and lead me to play again right away to see if I could achieve a different outcome. Its honestly one of the best little bits of the game in my opinion.\n\nOutside of the game itself, I should mention that I sent some feedback to the devs about the surrender mechanic (which is terrible, imo) which has  you click spamming to save a gladiator if they surrender. They got back to me in two days, and while their response was wishy washy, that's still a good turnaround for communication. Thought that was worth mentioning. \n\nOverall, its a good bit of fun, if not ground-breaking. On its own, I can't say I'd see it going for more than $10, and personally for what I got out of it I'd want to spend more like $5 - 8.", "comment_count": 0, "received_for_free": false, "voted_up": true, "recommendationid": "42084349", "weighted_vote_score": 0, "votes_up": 0, "steam_purchase": false, "timestamp_updated": 1526574813, "written_during_early_access": false, "votes_funny": 0}, {"timestamp_created": 1526553367, "language": "english", "author": {"steamid": "76561198370976714", "playtime_forever": 365, "last_played": 1546425244, "num_reviews": 13, "num_games_owned": 73, "playtime_last_two_weeks": 0}, "review": "6/10", "comment_count": 0, "received_for_free": false, "voted_up": true, "recommendationid": "42079598", "weighted_vote_score": 0, "votes_up": 0, "steam_purchase": false, "timestamp_updated": 1526553367, "written_during_early_access": false, "votes_funny": 0}, {"timestamp_created": 1526475082, "language": "english", "author": {"steamid": "76561198010724198", "playtime_forever": 928, "last_played": 1526115076, "num_reviews": 19, "num_games_owned": 952, "playtime_last_two_weeks": 0}, "review": "Nice style and good humour. Short but very interesting game. Story mode about 5 hours.", "comment_cou