o high\n\n-Blessings of Jupiter have the same issue as the tech tree; some perks are super OP and others are not. Spawn rate for worker-related blessings are way too low\n\n-Some workers are way more useful than others, especially when you consider the fact that when they are fired, their bonuses are removed\n\n-The architect's stone/fire pit/etc. upgrades take way too long to complete for the entire Ludum\n\n-Dialogue options often times do not feel like they have a lot of weight to them, and other times they feel like they are determinate upon random chance almost entirely\n\n-The Championship system makes it so that you can only challenge champions within about the last 100 days of the campaign\n\n-Min/maxing for anything other than strength feels useless, so naturally everyone will be doing this\n\nThose are all of the non-combat mechanics. Here is a list of combat issues I am seeing:\n\n-Lack of depth. You have four options: swing, block, roll, or throw weapon (which is too risky for no reward)\n\n-Impossible to separate yourself from enemies once the battle is started. No stunning, no sprinting, etc. \n\n-Missing essential combat mechanics like parrying, riposte, shield bash, etc. that I see in a ton of other melee combat games\n\n-Game would benefit immensely from a hold-power directional swing system, where the person will increase the power of their swing the longer they leave themselves open to hits and hold down the swing button\n\n-Group battles are a BLOODBATH. There is no way of strategizing to save all of your gladiators. You just have to hope and pray that they will all win, otherwise a common method would be to send one OP gladiator to kill the other group, which is just spammy and not fun\n\n-On a related note, Ludum composition is not important, because as mentioned earlier, classes have almost no differences between one another\n\n-A general lack of effects like blinding, cripple, etc. that dates all the way back to DnD and can add a ton of depth to combat as well\n\n-Generally feels like you are spamming the hit button between blocks, and at a certain point, blocking will literally not block all damage, and instead only a part\n\n\n\nOnce again, there are a lot of things about this game that I like, and I see so much potential for this to become a true classic game. but I am seeing way too many mechanics that have no thought put into them. The game is missing a huge amount of balance, and until it reaches the point where decisions in and out of combat have weight, I would have to tell the average consumer not to buy the game. \n\n\n\nEDIT: As of late, the dev has been releasing a lot of updates; About 1-2 per week. So far quite a few bugs have been handled, as well as some small gameplay changes. I see some potential for me to change my review in the future, but for now there have not been any monumental changes to the gameplay.", "comment_count": 0, "received_for_free": false, "voted_up": false, "recommendationid": "40747160", "weighted_vote_score": "0.577511906623840332", "votes_up": 6, "steam_purchase": true, "timestamp_updated": 1532308393, "written_during_early_access": false, "votes_funny": 0}, {"timestamp_created": 1520787150, "language": "english", "author": {"steamid": "76561198110749416", "playtime_forever": 212, "last_played": 1526020840, "num_reviews": 7, "num_games_owned": 386, "playtime_last_two_weeks": 0}, "review": "Gets one good Gladiator. Rename him sonic because he speeds around the arena one hitting all in his path. he is displeased by me renaming so i pay him a large sum of money and make him murder about 30 peaple so i can rearn the money. \n\n10/10 would op again", "comment_count": 0, "received_for_free": false, "voted_up": true, "recommendationid": "40746342", "weighted_vote_score": 0, "votes_up": 0, "steam_purchase": true, "timestamp_updated": 1520787150, "written_during_early_access": false, "votes_funny": 0}, {"timestamp_created": 1520762576, "language": "english", "author": {"st