al challenge because as long as I'm controlling one I always win.  Meditation (AI skill) shouldn't be something you train separately, but something that goes up automatically with each battle participated in.\n- On top of that, controlling the fighter basically amounts to spam left click, block if they attack until they roll or stop, spam again.  There's no stances or types of attacks, it's just spam clicking.  \n\nConclusion: I really really want to like this game, but the actual management aspect is extremely shallow and easy, the voice lines are just silly and kinda ruin the immersion, and the battle system itself could use a lot more depth, especially in regards to your allies - it seems like their goal isn't to win but just to kill themselves as fast as possible.\n\nI'm writing such a long review because I really do like this concept, and I think the game has a lot of potential.  I really hope the devs see this review and update some things because in it's current state it's just not worth the purchase.", "comment_count": 0, "received_for_free": false, "voted_up": false, "recommendationid": "40499709", "weighted_vote_score": "0.483760535717010498", "votes_up": 1, "steam_purchase": true, "timestamp_updated": 1519954776, "written_during_early_access": false, "votes_funny": 0}, {"timestamp_created": 1519938606, "language": "english", "author": {"steamid": "76561198030779908", "playtime_forever": 1870, "last_played": 1537760081, "num_reviews": 31, "num_games_owned": 1016, "playtime_last_two_weeks": 0}, "review": "I've put almost 24 hours into the game now and it is very good. I suggest that everyone should purchase it if they catch it on a sale. Either way it's worth the $10 price tag. There is more depth to the economy than you would expect in the beginning. The game is not difficult and you can pause the timer while training to do your tasks. This allows you to kick back instead of being rushed while you micro manage things. Once you get the hang of it things are