; this makes it incredibly easy to decide whose stats you want to increase from the fight (your warriors' stats increase massively if they win fights). If you only saw one opponent out of X, and drafted a champion in relation to only what you can see being put on the board by your opponent, the matchups would be much more balanced and interesting because I think you would need to have a greater variety of champions. For example, it would be wise to draft slaves or cannon fodder early in a draft in order to see what your opponent is willing to put on the board, then only put up your best champions toward the end of a draft if you really want to win that match. \n\nThe fights themselves do not see much variety. I found myself wishing that I could pit my best champion against 20 other lesser champions for a good show, but the game only gives you 5 opponents at most until the last battle. Also there seems to be little strategy or benefit to having a varied team. Dual wielders do boatloads of damage, and spearmen are agile and annoying, but when it comes to choosing a lineup against an opponent it doesn't really seem to matter the type of soldier you field. In fact the only thing that matters is HP and Damage -- if you have more of those stats, you will win. \n\nIt would be fun to have orders you could give before a match, and more experienced gladiators would do a better job of carrying out those orders. For example, you could tell your spearmen to stay in front of your other men, or play defensively until a net lands. Similarly, you could tell your dual wielder to parry and until the spearmen lands a net, then go in for a kill. Small strategy choices like this would help provide a feeling of management during battles that is simply missing right now. The crowd can throw weapons down into the pit, it would be nice if you could pay coin to throw weapons or even release animals in the middle of a fight. As is you are simply a spectator once the fight starts, unless of course you have mind control which I confess I have not even tried as it seems like a handicap more than anything. The AI is very quick at dodging and attacking, I would suggest letting them do it. \n\nOverall a cool game but I think it's obvious that the creators didn't take time to refine the game or balance it, they probably got it to a working state and released. With a few changes and balance tweaks it could be a great little game, worthy of being in any gamer's library if they love strategy and management games.", "comment_count": 0, "received_for_free": false, "voted_up": false, "recommendationid": "40453137", "weighted_vote_score": "0.479645490646362305", "votes_up": 1, "steam_purchase": true, "timestamp_updated": 1519791677, "written_during_early_access": false, "votes_funny": 0}, {"timestamp_created": 1519788452, "language": "english", "author": {"steamid": "76561198023301290", "playtime_forever": 237, "last_played": 1520560541, "num_reviews": 15, "num_games_owned": 159, "playtime_last_two_weeks": 0}, "review": "This game has an amazing soundtrack with the great gameplay.", "comment_count": 0, "received_for_free": false, "voted_up": true, "recommendationid": "40452379", "weighted_vote_score": 0, "votes_up": 0, "steam_purchase": true, "timestamp_updated": 1519788452, "written_during_early_access": false, "votes_funny": 0}, {"timestamp_created": 1519787517, "language": "english", "author": {"steamid": "76561198122022613", "playtime_forever": 39, "last_played": 1519787427, "num_reviews": 17, "num_games_owned": 57, "playtime_last_two_weeks": 0}, "review": "seems like fun but doesnt tell you how to play any of it. won a few fights, then it crashed", "comment_count": 0, "received_for_free": false, "voted_up": false, "recommendationid": "40452149", "weighted_vote_score": 0, "votes_up": 0, "steam_purchase": true, "timestamp_updated": 1530434649, "written_during_early_access": false, "votes_funny": 0}, {"timestamp_created": 1519787419, "language": "english", "author":