was so hidden in the UI I had to watch a YouTube stream of it to find out about it. Other things, like having your employees research different techs, has to be done manually in real time (so at the very least requires diligent pausing by the player). There is no option, as far as I can tell, to switch the management phase to a 'turn based' structure. \n\nThen combat. So at first glance it is automatic and AI driven - which is what I expected. However there is an early tech that allows you to control your gladiators in an 'ASWD+mouse clicking' sort of way. Based on streams it seems like you need to do this, since the early fighter AI is simply too poor (later it gets better). Again, this is not what was expected - the point of a management game is you don't have to manually click around in real time to do better. The last straw for me was when I researched a tech that allowed my gladiators to yield, and when I was losing a fight my gladiator yielded successfully. Phew. Then, before I realized what was going on, he was executed, apparently because I didn't button mash fast enough to save his life during a 'click fast to gain crowd favor for your yielded gladiator' mini game - I'm not interested.  \n\nThe pros of the game: the cool graphics, the incredible music, the interesting idea, are certainly there. For folks who want to dive in and manually control their fighters, this is probably a fun game. For people looking for a gladiator management sim, look elsewhere. \n\n(Also one minor quip for the developers: renaming a character should not have an in game effect, in this case a moral drop. Renaming is useful to track your fighters, and shouldn't be punished with an in game mechanic).", "comment_count": 0, "received_for_free": false, "voted_up": false, "recommendationid": "39594133", "weighted_vote_score": "0.481620579957962036", "votes_up": 9, "steam_purchase": true, "timestamp_updated": 1516843251, "written_during_early_access": false, "votes_funny": 1}, {"timestamp