s going. Its all very meh. \n\n- the game has no scaling. You either get pathetic dudes or steam trains. There is zero middle ground really. There are no fights that scale with your fighters. Generally my wweak fighters only get better during 5 on 5 matches where the death machine solos the entire enemy team in the time it took the newbie to cross the arena. \n\n- I completed it in 2 hours in one playthrough and accicdentally go tthe good ending. I didnt even know it was coming, I was just plodding along building a team of death machines when they informed me the finals were here. I thought I was severely unprepared hahahahaha....I was not. My team ran in and backhanded the \"champion of rome\" into the next decade. \n\n- there are tons of staff you can employ...but it is blindingly obvious which ones are necessary and you can only have 3 so half the game content becomes useless. (yeah, you are gonna need a medic and an architect for sure. for your last slot you have about 10 choices, 9 of which are meh and one of which is amazing.)\n\nthere are good parts to this game. the fighting is hilariously fun to watch, the music is 11/10 (it is absolutely banging) and it has a good team of devs who still make updates and changes but I find that for the game to be worth a recommend, it needs a complete balance overhaul along with something meaningful to do outside fights. I am however going to continue watching with earnest eyes and will change my review if I see substantial changes. \n\nIf its super cheap on a sale though....it is fun for a few hours at least.", "comment_count": 0, "received_for_free": false, "voted_up": false, "recommendationid": "38587906", "weighted_vote_score": 0, "votes_up": 0, "steam_purchase": true, "timestamp_updated": 1514050641, "written_during_early_access": false, "votes_funny": 1}, {"timestamp_created": 1514042743, "language": "english", "author": {"steamid": "76561198077529338", "playtime_forever": 392, "last_played": 1533419314, "num_reviews"