nch of your gladiators back when you were still in charge. Then they will come to your aid at the time of need. But you are never told that in the game. Sure, there is the option to grant freedom, but when you trained a killer gladiator who wins every fight, you don't think about getting rid of them.[/spoiler]\n\n[b]SPOILERS OVER![/b]\n\n[h1]Look...[/h1]\nIt has some very nice, pixel-art graphics. The thing I liked the most was the blood spatter in the arena. \n\n[h1]... and Feel[/h1]\nThings are not explained well enough. That's my main problem with this game. You go to the Options menu and you see there are key bindings to control your gladiator in the arena. So the fight begins, you try to move, but you can't and AI is in control of your fighter. I googled it straight away and it turns out that you need to develop the Mind Control ability to actually control your warriors. I wish that was explained somewhere in the game, without having to read the descriptions of all the abilities before you start playing.\n\n[h1]Music[/h1]\nIt's actually pretty good! It has nice and calm moments that match the game setting and atmosphere. And it can quickly turn into dynamic music that fits perfectly with arena battles. You can check out the whole thing on [url=https://bignic.bandcamp.com/album/domina]bignic's Band Camp page[/url].\n\n[h1]Gameplay[/h1]\nIt's resource management, mostly. You need to control your money, food, water and wine, while trying to expand and improve your ludus. Have your gladiators train on improving their stats and equip them with better weapons and armours. In the meantime your doctore will unlock new moves and skills for your fighters. You can also hire other specialists who will reduce training or healing times.\nYou have one year to get your gladiators ready for a big tournament. There are some regular fights that you can fight in, but you can also arrange additional ones or challenge arena legends in different areas of the map.\nEach victory will grant you more money, improved skills for the winners, potential new gladiators or improvement cards (Jupiter's Blessings) that you can use on your fighters or other employees to make them more efficient.\nThe fights in the arena are usually random. It's one or more of your gladiators against one or more enemies, often chained to the ground or supported by lions. You can control one of your fighters (after you unlock a skill) or have AI do that for you (the AI abilities can be improved with meditation training) - this is necessary during many vs many battles.\n\n[h1]Conclusion[/h1]\nIt's short and not that complicated, but still not explained well enough.\nI just wanted to play one more battle and I ended up finishing the game in one sitting. \nBut I don't feel like playing again.\n\n[h1]Pros[/h1]\n- nice pixel-art graphics\n- great soundtrack\n- short and fun while it lasts\n\n[h1]Cons[/h1]\n- some bits are not explained well enough\n- disappointing ending\n- fighting manually can be difficult with low level gladiators\n\n\n[quote][i]For more reviews, follow my Curator page[/i] - [b][url=http://store.steampowered.com/curator/31210849-Sublime-Dent/]Sublime Dent[/url][/b].[/quote]", "comment_count": 0, "received_for_free": false, "voted_up": true, "recommendationid": "36489778", "weighted_vote_score": "0.565217375755310059", "votes_up": 3, "steam_purchase": true, "timestamp_updated": 1527592982, "written_during_early_access": false, "votes_funny": 0}, {"timestamp_created": 1510544850, "language": "english", "author": {"steamid": "76561198031789432", "playtime_forever": 171, "last_played": 1510544729, "num_reviews": 169, "num_games_owned": 895, "playtime_last_two_weeks": 0}, "review": "Seemed easy, then it had a twist. Whoops.", "comment_count": 0, "received_for_free": true, "voted_up": true, "recommendationid": "36484748", "weighted_vote_score": "0.487903356552124023", "votes_up": 1, "steam_purchase": false, "timestamp_updated": 1510544868, "written_during_early_acces