e. Apparently, you can get past slaves to help you if you free them or something, but all I really did was free the ones I got that weren't already armoured and had classes that would only be sold for 2 gold so I didn't stand a chance. Also my frames absolutely died with an i5-6600k overclocked to 4.6 GHz and a 1060. I guess it was a lot of pixelated violence or something? Should my PC have dropped like 40 frames from that? I dunno. I'm not mad that the naked slave men didn't kill them, I'm mad that this scummy below-the-belt move just gets straight up pulled on you for no reason with next to no real warning.[/spoiler]\n\n\n\n\u1d1b\u029f;\u1d05\u0280\nDomina is an alrite game, I guess. A catchy but out of place soundtrack and a mildly fun early-mid game if you know what you're doing. But, it suffers from a boring, overpowered late-game, a frustrating early game when you first purchase it, and [spoiler]a bs ending.[/spoiler]\n\n\nThere's an endless mode but I didn't bother, I decided instead to refund it for my $5 back so I can buy something else. If it was 75% off, only like $2.49, I probably would have kept it, it has alrite replay value, but nothing substantial, but you can definitely get worse for the price, the game isn't bad by any means, but statistically, the cons outweigh the pros by quite a large margin.", "comment_count": 2, "received_for_free": false, "voted_up": false, "recommendationid": "33011362", "weighted_vote_score": "0.419615775346755981", "votes_up": 2, "steam_purchase": true, "timestamp_updated": 1498773079, "written_during_early_access": false, "votes_funny": 0}, {"timestamp_created": 1498771285, "language": "english", "author": {"steamid": "76561198004608407", "playtime_forever": 435, "last_played": 1500931559, "num_reviews": 41, "num_games_owned": 180, "playtime_last_two_weeks": 0}, "review": "Spent 6 hours during the last two days. Well spent 4.99 \u20ac. I'm not bored yet.", "comment_count": 0, "received_for_free": false, "voted_up": true,