epth tutorial will be added later on, though as a complete playthrough takes at most a couple of hours (including plenty of pausing to take breaks) the priority at the moment is fixing any game breaking bugs that a few people have encountered.\n\nAt the time of writing this review, I have played a total of about 21 hours, and have beaten the game twice, once on normal difficulty and once on hard. It may be quite a while before I attempt the masochistic pro-gamer setting. If you've got enough time to watch a film occasionally then you've got enough time to beat this game. If you think you might enjoy the spectacle, my only advice is this: playing with modern day human ethical standards may be hazardous to your wallet, your health and your ultimate fate. However, playing like an absolute <expletive> may well come back to haunt you.\n\nIf you think you've got what it takes to make your fortune while the largest empire the world has ever known collapses around you, then show these fighting men the power of Domina.\n\nCarpe noctem.", "comment_count": 0, "received_for_free": false, "voted_up": true, "recommendationid": "31207497", "weighted_vote_score": 0, "votes_up": 0, "steam_purchase": true, "timestamp_updated": 1492464730, "written_during_early_access": false, "votes_funny": 0}, {"timestamp_created": 1492448840, "language": "english", "author": {"steamid": "76561197975756797", "playtime_forever": 1762, "last_played": 1531813593, "num_reviews": 5, "num_games_owned": 197, "playtime_last_two_weeks": 0}, "review": "Most of the complaints I've read can be overcome through in game mechanics or upgrades, the people either dont know how to or didn't even try. The only complaints I have is low replayability when finished, no endless mode, no save function. Even if that save function ensured that dead gladiators stayed dead (No quitting without saving, autosaves fights) it would be fine, I like the rogue-like aspect. \n\nProtip: Use mind control, spearmen are the best in the ga