ights can seem rather one sided against you. At first it'll be easy if a bit challenging and then suddenly the AI will seem to crank up the difficulty to death metal.\n\nSo the game is pretty hard. Like, take Enter the Gungeon difficulty and double it kind of hard. Like Dark Souls except you get sent back to the beggening every time kind of hard. Some wierdos like me will enjoy it, normal people will play it much to their chagrin. Or, you know, you could read a manual.\n\nAlright, time for the...\n\n[b]Pros[/b]\n\nThe biggest pro, in my opinion, is the game's [b]soundtrack.[/b] The game's soundtrack was created by the developer himself, which is why it seems to fit almost perfectly into the game. The way the music weaves in and out of arena fights and moments of calm is rather well set up. If you like the 8-bit, retro-y electronic tracks of Hotline Miami and Deadbolt, you'll like Domina's soundtrack.\n\nThe arena fights can be a little too fast paced in my taste, but they are a nice comfortable combo of [b]brutal and random.[/b] Weapons do enough damage that they actually feel like they're weapons and not kitchen utencils, armor makes a significant change to the performance of a gladiator, for better or worse, and yet somehow the game retains a comfy level of random elements so that even someone who is outgunned in every way still might just win. (There are a lot of funny stories about half naked slaves somehow slaughtering well equipped opponents thanks to the generosity of Rome's fine citizens)\n\nWhile we're on the line of good mixes, Domina is also a great mix between [b]careful strategy and fast past brutal action.[/b] It goes without saying that a game about managing a gladiatior school would be part gladiating part schooling and it pulls it off well, making choices in and out of the pit matter.\n\n-----\n\nOver all, I recommend the game for [i]my[/i] kind of game player. If you have a lot of time on your hands and enjoy electronic kinda music, this is definitly a game you would like. If not, if you're a normal person that doesn't like to play impossible games or just simply doesn't want to invest a game he will probably never beat, that's fine too I guess.\n\nOverall 8/10 dead gladiators.", "comment_count": 0, "received_for_free": false, "voted_up": true, "recommendationid": "31030743", "weighted_vote_score": "0.528057277202606201", "votes_up": 3, "steam_purchase": true, "timestamp_updated": 1493087707, "written_during_early_access": false, "votes_funny": 0}, {"timestamp_created": 1491695819, "language": "english", "author": {"steamid": "76561198080031173", "playtime_forever": 333, "last_played": 1492295954, "num_reviews": 5, "num_games_owned": 772, "playtime_last_two_weeks": 0}, "review": "Great game, but lacks any depth.", "comment_count": 1, "received_for_free": false, "voted_up": false, "recommendationid": "31029006", "weighted_vote_score": "0.443661987781524658", "votes_up": 0, "steam_purchase": true, "timestamp_updated": 1491695819, "written_during_early_access": false, "votes_funny": 0}, {"timestamp_created": 1491695628, "language": "english", "author": {"steamid": "76561198008582160", "playtime_forever": 1218, "last_played": 1532971257, "num_reviews": 47, "num_games_owned": 481, "playtime_last_two_weeks": 0}, "review": "There are issues with the game, like I cannot make sense of the gladiators and the AI in general. Like the top review by \n\nMaster Debater says: \"Overwhelmingly what I see is that no matter the opponents stats, the enemy AI will attack first and faster as well as dodge and block more more effectively. I have had gladiators who weigh less, have higher aggro, higher AI skill, and higher agility than the opponent who do not even get a single hit on them, because they are repeatedly struck with attacks that are commited with higher frequency AND swung more quickly than they are able to perform.\"\n\nThis is my exact same experience.\n\nBut it dosen't mean it isn't fun, and that is the most importan